  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200&deg;C/ 180&deg;C (fan)/ 400&deg;F/ Gas 6</p>\r\n<p>Cut the&nbsp;<strong>potatoes</strong>&nbsp;(skins on) into bite-sized pieces&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add the<strong> potatoes</strong> to a baking tray, drizzle them with <strong>olive oil</strong> and season generously with <strong>salt</strong>, then toss them gently to coat&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Place the tray in the oven until step 4 (approx. 10 min)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/768.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/768.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/768.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/768.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/768.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic </strong></p>\r\n<p>Strip the<strong> rosemary</strong> leaves from the stalks and chop finely</p>\r\n<p>Grind the <strong>hazelnuts&nbsp;</strong>in a<strong> pestle &amp; mortar</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>rosemary</strong>, <strong>ground hazelnuts</strong> and <strong>breadcrumbs</strong> to a mixing bowl with&nbsp;2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span>&nbsp;<strong>olive oil </strong>&amp; season with a large pinch of&nbsp;<strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>\r\n<p>Melt 40g <span class=\"text-danger\">[80g]</span>&nbsp;<strong>butter</strong> in a pan and once melted, add it to the <strong>nut mixture</strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/768.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/768.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/768.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/768.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/768.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Pat the <strong>pork tenderloin's</strong> dry with kitchen paper</p>\r\n<p>Add the pork to the<strong> nut mixture</strong></p>\r\n<p>Use your hands to firmly press the nut mixture onto the tenderloins so they're&nbsp;fully coated &ndash; this is your <strong>hazelnut crusted pork&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/768.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/768.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/768.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/768.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/768.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Place the<strong> hazelnut crusted</strong>&nbsp;<strong>pork</strong>&nbsp;and any spare <strong>nut&nbsp;mixture</strong>&nbsp;over the potatoes</p>\r\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 20 min or until the pork&nbsp;is cooked and the potatoes are crispy&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
